    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) features the refined 3.6L M96 flat-six, delivering 320 hp through a crisp 6-speed manual transaxle. The IMS bearing has been addressed with a dual-row ceramic upgrade, ensuring long-term structural integrity of the rotating assembly. It retains its factory-correct M030 sport suspension geometry, augmented by Bilstein B8 dampers for improved compression and rebound characteristics. The braking system utilizes four-piston monobloc calipers over cross-drilled rotors, providing consistent thermal management. While the Arctic Silver metallic finish shows minor road-derived patina, the mechanical synchronization and throttle response remain razor-sharp. A driver-focused example with a clean DME report and documented service intervals.",
